      "date": "2012-01-06 06:12:43.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(1 inline comment)\n\nI think it makes more sense to leave parse_size() to parse arbitrary passed strings, and then check in the caller when a negative value is not permitted.\n\nstatic int lfs_setstripe(int argc, char **argv)\n{\n\n        /* get the stripe size */\n        if (stripe_size_arg != NULL) {\n                result = parse_size(stripe_size_arg, &st_size, &size_units, 0);\n                if (result || st_size < 0) {\n                        fprintf(stderr, \"error: %s: bad stripe_size '%s'\\n\",\n                                argv[0], stripe_size_arg);\n                        return result;\n                }\n        }\n\nThe error message is also improved a bit to report that this is the stripe size.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
